We reiterated our recommendation that Management:

Direct Officers and Employees with cash advances to immediately submit their liquidation papers or refund the amount advanced, otherwise, require the immediate withholding of salary of those officers and employees who were unable to comply with the requirement; 

Require the Municipal Accountant to closely monitor the liquidation of outstanding cash advances and regularly send written demand on the submission of liquidation report or refund thereof. Moreover, look into the details of the Due from Officers and Employees account and reclassify to the Advances to Officers and Employees account amounts pertaining to advances for travel and ensure that proper accounts are used in recording the transactions pertaining to cash advances; 

Stop the practice of granting additional cash advances to those who have unliquidated cash advances unless the previous ones are fully settled; and

File a request for authority to write-off dormant or long outstanding unliquidated cash advances to the Office of the Auditor following the guidelines and procedures in COA Circular No. 2016-005.

We recommended that Management:

Implement immediately and on timely basis the identified PPAs under the 20 per cent DF.  The Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator and other concerned Head of Offices must monitor the implementation of the projects to fast tract its completion;

Prepare and submit the distribution of the lump sum appropriation and utilization of the same, if warranted.  Also, the Municipal Budget Officer prepare the budget based on the duly approved AIP indicating each PPA specifically and identify the expected outputs for each PPAs with their corresponding appropriation. For those appropriations already presented in lump sum that are not yet implemented, a separate SB appropriation ordinance be secured by the Municipal Mayor to serve as an authority to enter into contract in behalf of the Municipal Government;

Require the Municipal Accountant to strictly adhere with the timing on withholding taxes and observe proper recording of accounts; 

Establish guidelines or criteria for the grant of livelihood assistance to indigent constituents. Also, require the Municipal Accountant to recognize Loans Receivable - Others account and make necessary adjustments in the government equity accounts; and

Require the contractors to post warranty security for all completed and accepted projects.

We recommended that Management:

Ensure that planned PPAs for SEF are optimally implemented/utilized for the efficient and timely delivery of targeted services and benefits to the constituents in accordance with the proper utilization of the fund; 

Include the previous years’ unexpended balances, as well as the continuing appropriation, in determining the net amount available for appropriation;

